title: New license plate part of Rhode Island's rebranding
text: New license plate part of Rhode Island's rebranding Governor Raimondo says campaign has to be 'all in' Comment Posted Oct. 1, 2015 at 6:40 PM By Kate BramsonJournal Staff Writer Posted Oct. 1, 2015 at 6:40 PM PROVIDENCE, R.I. — New license plates for Rhode Islanders are part of the effort to rebrand the state with a new tourism and business-attraction campaign, Governor Raimondo assured the Commerce Corporation's board of directors Wednesday before they approved negotiations with marketing firms. Even though the state is due for new plates, Raimondo said she has held up that design process so it will coincide with a new state brand — "because if we're going to do this, we've got to be all in." Just as Michigan is, she said, with its Pure Michigan campaign. On a family trip to Michigan last weekend, Raimondo told the board, she recognized anew: "These people are all in." By Kate Bramson
